1911 Dan Wesson Pointman 9 (10 + 1 9mm)

The Dan Wesson Pointman 9 is the only Government 5” size Dan Wesson 1911 chambered in 9mm Luger.  Dan Wesson has offered this pistol in limited production quantities over the last few years. Demand for this pistol has always been greater than production capacity allowed.

The PM9 features the Dan Wesson version of the Clark style rib on top of a forged slide, and an adjustable target sight in the rear and a red fiber optic sight in the front.

The slide also features DW’s custom front and rear cocking serrations. The frame is forged stainless steel with an undercut trigger guard and 25 LPI front strap checkering. DW polished the flat surfaces of the pistol to a soft-brushed finish and sandblasted the rounded surfaces for a beautiful contrast. This pretty pistol is finished off with Double Diamond Cocobolo wood grips.

With the low cost of 9mm ammo, and the lack of recoil, this is a perfect model for comfortable shooting and for competition shooting. Women should have no trouble shooting this pistol.

The pistol comes with two DW 9 round magazines and two 10 round Wilson Combat magazines (a $76 bonus). Add one in the chamber for maximum capacity. The trigger on this pistol has been tuned by a gunsmith and is appropriate for match or competition shooting.  A fitted Smith and Alexander magwell has been installed by the same gunsmith for ease of magazine changes. The magwell and gunsmithing cost $125 together.

The DAN WESSON ADVERTISED PRICE is $1,558.00, if they are available from DW. Instead of that $1,558 price plus the $90 magwell, plus the $76 extra magazines, plus the $50 gunsmithing, you can buy this pistol in like new condition with all of the original factory items for $1,250.00.
